  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
    <subfield code="a">In 3-dimensional pure Einstein gravity, the geometries of the vacuum space-times are always trivial, and gravitational wave (graviton) is strictly forbidden. For the first time we find a vacuum circularly symmetric black hole with nontrivial geometries in $f(R)$ gravity theory, in which a true singularity appears. In this frame with non-trivial geometry, perturbative gravitational wave does exist. Beyond perturbative level, we make a constructive proof of the existence of gravitational wave. The Birkhoff-like theorem becomes invalid. We find exact solutions of circularly symmetric pure gravitational wave for radiation and absorption, respectively. This study may shed light on the microscopic origins of the entropy of 3-dimensional black hole, and further on the quantum theory of gravity in 3-dimensional space-time.</subfield>
  </datafield>
